 Go to SQL Server Management Studio and use the SQL Script to create your ODS Database and tables. This creates all the tables. Run the script below in Management Studio:

  •          ConsumerComplaints-CreateODS20210604.sql

Confirm in Management Studio that the objects have been created by right clicking on the Database tab and selecting Refresh. Then run script provided to create all the table objects.  See below Screen:

Step 3.       

1.     In SSIS Toolbox Double click on a Sequence Container to bring onto the designer pane, rename it as SC_ Dictionaery_Product

2.     Also double click the Data flow Task – that bring it in canvas – Rename as DFT _ LoadDictionary_Product, place the DFT inside the Sequence container and double click the DFT to open it up and build the package as follows:




3.  Click and drag _OLE DB Source, rename as OLEDB_tbl_Stg_ConsumerComplaints,

     Open to configure OLEDB Source Editor, Connection Manager

– Select ConsumerComplaints_Staging

     4.    Select SQL Command text instead of Table  SQL Query

              SELECT      Product, SubProduct, DateReceived, ComplaintID       

              FROM         tbl_Stg_ComsumerComplaints         

              WHERE      (Product IN NOT NULL) AND (SubProduct IS NOT NULL)

            For Different Dictionary Tables - The SQL Query is located within the Data Mapping Excel file



5.  Click and drag derived column – Configure Editor to create

     CreatedBy and ModifiedBy columns

6.  Click and drag in Data Conversion Configure Editor as shown below




7.  Click and drag Lookup Transformation – configure as shown

8.  Click and drag OLEDB Destination rename as OLEDB Destination _ Dictionary_Product - Connect to Lookup Match Output to OLEDB Destination

9. Lookup No Match to Multicast Task




The same steps 1 - 9 will be repeated to build the package that will load the other dictionary tables in the ODS from the Staging database

The changes that need to be made are renaming the package, using  appropriately SQL Query, proper data selection and mapping. for the following  dictionary tables:

·       Dictionary_Complaint

·       Dictionary_Company

·       Dictionary_TypeOfIssue

·       Dictionary_Location

·       Dictionary_ComplainantINFO




 4.    Select SQL Command text instead of Table  SQL Query

SQL Query:

SELECT      ComplaintWhatHappened, ConsumerConsentProvided,  

  Tags, DateReceived, DateSentToCompany, SubmittedVia, ComplaintID

FROM     tbl_Stg_ConsumerComplaints                                      

WHERE       (ComplaintWhatHappened IS NOT NULL) AND TAGS IS NOT NULL 

ORDER BY    ComplaintID




5.    Select SQL Command text instead of Table  SQL Query

SQL Query:

SELECT Company,CompanyPublicResponse, CompanyResponse, Timely, DateReceived

FROM [dbo].[tbl_Stg_ConsumerComplaints]

WHERE CompanyPublicResponse IS NOT NULL




6.    Select SQL Command text instead of Table  SQL Query

SQL Query:

SELECT        Issue, SubIssue, DateReceived

FROM          tbl_Stg_ConsumerComplaints

WHERE        (Issue IS NOT NULL) AND (SubIssue IS NOT NULL)



7.    Select SQL Command text instead of Table  SQL Query

SQL Query:

SELECT        State, ZipCode, DateReceived

FROM          tbl_Stg_ConsumerComplaints

WHERE        (State IS NOT NULL) AND (ZipCode IS NOT NULL)





 Step 4:  Build the ODS layer Package and Load the layer from Staging Database

- Click and drag  Data Flow Task rename as DFT_ Load _tbl_ConsumerComplaints_ODS - The package is then build to load the Fact table from ODS database as shown below

- Click and drag a Sequence Container, rename as SC_tbl_ConsumerComplaint_ODS, place the the DFT inside the SC 

      

             

   1.  Click and drag OLE DB Source >> Rename as OLE DB_ConsumerComplaints_Stg, Configure the Editor to connect to Staging database and select tbl_Stg_ConsumerComplaints table

      

 

  2.   Click and drag Lookup Transformation Task >>[Rename LKP_Dictionary_Complaint]

         Configure the Lookup Transformation Editor as follows:

        General       Cache mode >> Select Full cache

                                 Connection type >> Select OLEDB connection manger

                                 Specify how to handle rows with no matching entries

                               >> Select Redirect rows to no matching output

       Connection   OLE DB connection manager:

                            >> Select ServerName.ComsumerComplaints_ODS

                           Use a table or a view >> Select the [dbo].[Dictionary_Complaint]  to Lookup

ComplaintID

       Columns  >> Select [Tick] ComplaintID connect a least one matching record from the  “Available Input Columns” to the “Available Lookup Columns”  >>>Then click OK

      

   

 Click and drag new Lookup Task >> connect the Lookup together selecting “Lookup Match Output

Repeat the above steps to configure the Lookup Task for the following Lookup

3.        ProductID          [Dictionary_Product]

4.        CompanyID      [Dictionary_Company]

5.        LocationID        [Dictionary_Location]

6.        IssueID                [Dictionary_TypeOfIssue]


7.     Click and drag Derived Column Transformation Task on to the designer pane, connect it and create the columns

            -       CreatedBy

            -       ModifiedBy

 8.    Click and drag the OLE DB Destination. Rename as OLE DB_Destination_tbl ConsumerComplaints_ODS and connect to the Derived Column                                                           

     


 Step  6.       Drag and drop Execute SQL Task from the SSIS Toolbox onto the canvas

 Configure the Execute SQL Task to initialize the dictionary tables by truncating all previous data by providing the query and screenshot  below in the SQL Statement Tab
